parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: Pagination token used to paginate output. When this value is provided as input, the service returns results from where the previous response left off. When this value is present in output, it indicates that there are more results to retrieve.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: The total number of records to return in the command's output. If the total number of records available is more than the value specified, nextToken is provided in the command's output. To resume pagination, provide the nextToken output value in the nextToken argument of a subsequent command. Do not use the nextToken response element directly outside of the Amazon CLI.

nested_items.name: tasks
nested_items.description: The requested list of import tasks.

nested_items.name: graphId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Neptune Analytics graph.

nested_items.name: taskId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the import task.

nested_items.name: source
nested_items.description: A URL identifying to the location of the data to be imported. This can be an Amazon S3 path, or can point to a Neptune database endpoint or snapshot.

nested_items.name: format
nested_items.description: Specifies the format of S3 data to be imported. Valid values are CSV, which identifies the Gremlin CSV format or OPENCYPHER, which identies the openCypher load format.

nested_items.name: parquetType
nested_items.description: The parquet type of the import task.

nested_items.name: roleArn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the IAM role that will allow access to the data that is to be imported.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: Pagination token used to paginate output.
